
[1]readiness

   READINESS, n. red'iness. [from ready.]

   1. Quickness; promptness; promptitude; facility; freedom from
   hinderance or obstruction; as readiness of speech; readiness of
   thought; readiness of mind in suggesting an answer; readiness of reply.

   2. Promptitude; cheerfulness; willingness; alacrity; freedom from
   reluctance; as, to grant a request or assistance with readiness.

   They received the word with all readiness of mind. Acts 17.

   3. A state of preparation; fitness of condition. The troops are in
   readiness.
